1. dbt init

2. dbt --config-dir   -- This is to check the profiles.yml file of your dbt project


3. # TO install dependencies

dbt deps 


4. # To generate model using dbt command :  (This is only possible if you have codegen package)

dbt run-operation generate_base_model --args '{"source_name": "thelook_ecommerce", "table_name": "orders"}'


5. # To generate model yaml file command :

 dbt run-operation generate_model_yaml --args '{"model_names": ["stg_ecommerce__orders"]}'


6.# running dbt model 

 dbt run -s stg_ecommerece__orders 

7. # full refresh will drop the view and create it as table , if view is present in with same name in bq but in dbt_project.yml the setting is : 
models:
  asmit_prj:
    +materialized: table

 dbt run -s stg_ecommerce__orders --full-refresh

  
  if we mention persistent docs setting in dbt_project.yml ,  while running the model and creating the table, the descrition will be generated in bq if its mentioned in repecitive yml file 

+persist_docs: 
      relation: true 
      columns: true



 8. The dbt clean command removes all directories specified in the clean-targets list of your dbt_project.yml file, primarily deleting the target/ (compiled SQL) and dbt_packages/ (or dbt_modules/) directories. 
 It is used to reset a project, remove obsolete artifacts, or ensure a clean environment before reinstalling dependencies.

  dbt clean 
  dbt deps 


9.  testing dbt model 

  dbt test -s  dbt run -s stg_ecommerece__orders 


10. dbt run    - This command causes to run all the models present in your project 


11. dbt test  - This command causes to test all the models present in your project 


12. dbt build - This command causes to run all the models followed by the testing of  dbt models in the project .


